Package: ssftpd
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends},
         ${misc:Depends},
         openssl,
         libjsoncpp4,
         adduser,
         systemd-sysv | sysvinit-core
Recommends: logrotate
Suggests: ssftpd-doc
Description: Simple-Secure FTP Daemon
 Simple-Secure FTP Daemon (ssftpd) is a secure, configurable FTP server with
 modular architecture. It supports SSL/TLS encryption, virtual hosting, user
 authentication, and rate limiting.
 .
 Features:
  * SSL/TLS encryption support
  * Virtual hosting with JSON configuration
  * Modular architecture (enable/disable features)
  * User authentication and authorization
  * Rate limiting and DDoS protection
  * Comprehensive logging and monitoring
  * Cross-platform support (Linux, macOS, Windows)
 .
 This package contains the main server binary and configuration files.

Package: ssftpd-dev
Architecture: any
Section: libdevel
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends},
         ${misc:Depends},
         ssftpd (= ${binary:Version})
Description: Development files for Simple-Secure FTP Daemon
 This package contains development files for ssftpd, including headers and
 libraries needed for developing applications that use ssftpd.
 .
 This package is only needed if you want to develop applications that use
 ssftpd libraries.

Package: ssftpd-doc
Architecture: all
Section: doc
Depends: ${misc:Depends}
Description: Documentation for Simple-Secure FTP Daemon
 This package contains comprehensive documentation for ssftpd, including:
  * User guides and tutorials
  * Configuration examples
  * API documentation
  * Deployment guides
  * SSL certificate management
  * Troubleshooting guides
